                                       <p style="font-family:Avenir,Helvetica,sans-serif;box-sizing:border-box;color:#000;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5em;margin-top:0;text-align:left">Today’s Tips: <strong><u>How to submit a blog</u></strong></p>
                                       <p><span style="font-weight: 600;">Tip 1:</span> Think about a compelling topic. You are on the front lines and you likely hear the same questions over and over about health, about conditions & symptoms. These are the topics you should be considering as blog content. Share your knowledge and position yourself as an expert in your vertical. </p>
                                       <p><span style="font-weight: 600;">Tip 2:</span> Don’t sell. A blog should focus on tips and tricks, clients experience, health challenges that have been resolved because of your initiative, misconceptions about your profession, etc. If you are just focusing on making a sale it comes through in your writing. If you focus on what’s in it for the reader’ it will come across more consultative and real.</p>
                                       <p><span style="font-weight: 600;">Tip 3:</span> Short and sweet. A blog is a short information piece so using subheadings and bullet points to break out ideas is a great way to get to the point quickly and clearly.</p>
                                       <p><span style="font-weight: 600;">Tip 4:</span> Tell the reader a bit about you. At the end of the blog include a short bio about you and your company. We will link it to the appropriate pages and listing on the site.</p>
                                       <p><span style="font-weight: 600;">Tip 5:</span> Rely on the Health Squad community. Maybe a health professional, a member of Health Squad on the other side of the country had an idea about a treatment or service you already provide – why don’t you share that same article... My Health Squad is a community; each professional contributes to increase the visibility of the profession. Who knows, one day a blog with your name on it might be featured by a colleague on the other side of the planet.</p>
                                       <p><span style="font-weight: 600;">Tip 6:</span> Ghostwriters. If you have a great idea but don’t have the time or don’t think you have the talent to write a blog on your own, ask us how you can hire one of our talented content experts to write a series for you!</p>
